\title{First Coro concert finished}
\author{liamoc}
\date{2026-05-10}
\p{I successfully performed in [my first concert with Coro](loc-0049). I think it went very well, and I saw some familiar faces in the audience (including [[muehlboeck]]!). The programme was a very nice (although eclectic) collection of music
spanning centuries. Some of my favourites included Lobo's [Versa est in luctum](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fZ_FeBMsIlw),  Stravinsky's [Ave Maria](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Luh-UlFvxEk), the Agnus Dei movements from all of Byrd's Masses, including the [Byrd 5](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TXvvnypcg6k), and Morten Lauridsen's [O Magnum Mysterium](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tZ-nuU-hda8). It was a delight to sing with these talented singers and I'm looking forward to our next concert later in the year!  }
